EmailTemplate.subject: SunPower Request URGENT: Your Insurance info needs updating
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear {!Business_Registration__c.Account__c},
Thank you for participating in the SunPower Installation Partner Program and for your investment in changing the way the world is powered.
One of the requirements of the SunPower Installation Partner Program is to keep your enrollment information up to date. As such, one or more of the fields below are expired, expiring, or incomplete in CA:
General Liability Expiry: {!Business_Registration__c.Site_General_Liability_Exp__c} Auto Coverage Expiry: {!Business_Registration__c.Automotive_Expiration_Date__c} Workers Comp Expiry: {!Business_Registration__c.Site_Worker_Comp_Exp__c} Build Risk Expiry: {!Business_Registration__c.Builders_Risk_Expiration__c} Solar Contractor/Electrician/General Contractor Licenses: {!Business_Registration__c.Expires_On__c}
Lapsed insurance and licenses can prevent shipment and installation, and cause financial penalty to IP.
Attached is Article 17 Insurance & Licenses Requirements and a sample of ACORD Certificate of Liability Insurance. You can also view the Insurance and Licenses Requirement document in your signed MSA. Any of these documents will help you identify what is required and how to submit.
NOTE: SunPower must be named on each policy and in the Certificate Holder section of the ACORD format. Please use the following address:
SunPower Corporation 1414 Harbour Way South Richmond, CA 94804 Attn: Projects Administrator
Please also make sure to send a copy of all documents to Ma.Cristina.deBorja@sunpowercorp.com, RAcompliance@sunpowercorp.comand copy your Installation Partner Manager.
Thank you for your attention to this email.
SunPower Team
